sentences: Physical limitations did not diminish his output as a composer, and he unveiled new material on YouTube in 2012.
Jackson joined trumpeter Wadada Leo Smith's Golden Quartet with pianist Vijay Iyer and double-bassist John Lindberg in 2005.
He played with the Punk Funk All Stars in 2006, which included Melvin Gibbs, Joseph Bowie, Vernon Reid, and James Blood Ulmer.
In 2008 Jackson and Jamaaladeen Tacuma toured Europe with The Last Poets; this collaboration was documented in the film "The Last Poets / Made in Amerikkka" directed by Claude Santiago.
In 2011 Jackson, Vernon Reid and Melvin Gibbs formed a power trio called Encryption.

On July 7, 2012, Jackson performed at the Kessler Theater in Dallas with the latest version of the Decoding Society, which includes violinist Leonard Hayward, trumpeter John Weir, guitarist Gregg Prickett, and bassist Melvin Gibbs.
The performance was voted as one of the Ten Best Concerts of 2012 in the Dallas Observer.
Jackson died of leukemia on October 19, 2013, aged 73.
